Deadly Simplicity				KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Deadly Simplicity			SOURCEPAGE:p.121	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 01.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,01	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=01			PRETEXT:Prerequisites deity with a simple favored weapon, trained with your deity's favored weapon	DESC:Your deity's weapon is especially powerful in your hands. When you are wielding your deity's favored weapon, increase the damage die size of that weapon by one step. If your deity's favored weapon is an unarmed attack (such as a fist, if you worship Irori) and its damage die is smaller than d6, instead increase its damage die size to d6.
Domain Initiate				KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Domain Initiate			SOURCEPAGE:p.121	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 01.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,01	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=01																				DESC:Your deity bestows a special spell related to their powers. Select one domaina subject of particular interest to you within your religionfrom your deity's list. You gain an initial domain spell for that domain, a spell unique to the domain and not available to other clerics. Each domain's theme and domain spells appear in Table 8-2: Domains on page 441. Domain spells are a type of focus spell. It costs 1 Focus Point to cast a focus spell, and you start with a focus pool of 1 Focus Point. You refill your focus pool during your daily preparations, and you can regain 1 Focus Point by spending 10 minutes using the Refocus activity to pray to your deity or do service toward their causes. Focus spells are automatically heightened to half your level rounded up. Focus spells don't require spell slots, nor can you cast them using spell slots. Certain feats can give you more focus spells and increase the size of your focus pool, though your focus pool can never hold more than 3 Focus Points. The full rules for focus spells appear on page 301. Special You can select this feat multiple times, selecting a different domain each time and gaining its domain spell.	STACK:YES	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE					BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Domain Spell|1	BONUS:VAR|ClericDomain|1
Harming Hands				KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Harming Hands			SOURCEPAGE:p.121	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 01.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,01	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=01			PRETEXT:Prerequisites harmful font												DESC:The mordant power of your negative energy grows. When you cast harm, you roll d10s instead of d8s.
Healing Hands				KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Healing Hands			SOURCEPAGE:p.121	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 01.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,01	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=01			PRETEXT:Prerequisites healing font												DESC:Your positive energy is even more vibrant and restorative. When you cast heal, you roll d10s instead of d8s.
Holy Castigation				KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Holy Castigation			SOURCEPAGE:p.121	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 01.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,01	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=01			PRETEXT:Prerequisites good alignment											DESC:You combine holy energy with positive energy to damage demons, devils, and their evil ilk. Heal spells you cast damage fiends as though they were undead.
Reach Spell [One-Action]		KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Reach Spell				SOURCEPAGE:p.122	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 01.CLERIC.CONCENTRATE.METAMAGIC	PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,01	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=01																				DESC:You can extend the range of your spells. If the next action you use is to Cast a Spell that has a range, increase that spell's range by 30 feet. As is standard for increasing spell ranges, if the spell normally has a range of touch, you extend its range to 30 feet.
Cantrip Expansion				KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Cantrip Expansion			SOURCEPAGE:p.122	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 02.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,02	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=02																				DESC:You study a wider range of simple spells. You can prepare two additional cantrips each day.
Communal Healing				KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Communal Healing			SOURCEPAGE:p.122	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 02.CLERIC.HEALING.POSITIVE		PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,02	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=02																				DESC:You're a conduit for positive energy, and as you channel it through you, it heals some of your minor injuries. When you cast the heal spell to heal a single creature other than yourself, you regain Hit Points equal to the spell level of the heal spell.
Emblazon Armament				KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Emblazon Armament			SOURCEPAGE:p.122	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 02.CLERIC.EXPLORATION		PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,02	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=02																				DESC:Carefully etching a sacred image into a physical object, you steel yourself for battle. You can spend 10 minutes emblazoning a symbol of your deity upon a weapon or shield. The symbol doesn't fade until 1 year has passed, but if you Emblazon an Armament, any symbol you previously emblazoned and any symbol already emblazoned on that item instantly disappears. The item becomes a religious symbol of your deity and can be used as a divine focus while emblazoned, and it gains another benefit determined by the type of item. This benefit applies only to followers of the deity the symbol represents. &nl;Shield The shield gains a +1 status bonus to its Hardness. (This causes it to reduce more damage with the Shield Block reaction.) &nl;Weapon The wielder gains a +1 status bonus to damage rolls.
Sap Life					KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Sap Life				SOURCEPAGE:p.122	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 02.CLERIC.HEALING			PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,02	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=02																				DESC:You draw the life force out of your enemies to heal your own wounds. When you cast a harm spell and damage at least one living creature, you regain Hit Points equal to the spell level of your harm spell. If you aren't a living creature, you gain no benefit from this feat.
Turn Undead					KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Turn Undead				SOURCEPAGE:p.122	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 02.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,02	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=02																				DESC:Undead harmed by your positive energy might flee, compelled by an innate aversion to the force opposite undeath. When you use a heal spell to damage undead, each undead of your level or lower that critically fails its save gains the fleeing condition for 1 round.
Versatile Font				KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Versatile Font			SOURCEPAGE:p.122	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 02.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,02	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=02			PRETEXT:Prerequisites harmful font or healing font, deity that allows clerics to have both fonts	DESC:As you explore your deity's aspects, you move beyond restrictions on healing or harming. You can prepare either harm or heal in the spell slots gained from the harmful font or healing font.
Channel Smite [Two-Actions]		KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Channel Smite			SOURCEPAGE:p.122	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 04.CLERIC.DIVINE.NECROMANCY	PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,04	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=04			PRETEXT:Prerequisites harmful font or healing font									DESC:Cost Expend a harm or heal spell. &nl;You siphon the destructive energies of positive or negative energy through a melee attack and into your foe. Make a melee Strike and add the spell's damage to the Strike's damage. This is negative damage if you expended a harm spell or positive damage if you expended a heal spell. The spell is expended with no effect if your Strike fails or hits a creature that isn't damaged by that energy type (such as if you hit a non-undead creature with a heal spell).
Command Undead [One-Action]		KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Command Undead			SOURCEPAGE:p.123	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 04.CLERIC.CONCENTRATE.METAMAGIC	PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,04	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=04			PRETEXT:Prerequisites harmful font, evil alignment									DESC:You grasp the animating force within an undead creature and bend it to your will. If the next action you use is to cast harm targeting one undead creature, you transform the effects of that harm spell. Instead of harm's normal effects, the target becomes controlled by you if its level is equal to or lower than your level - 3. It can attempt a Will saving throw to resist being controlled by you. If the target is already under someone else's command, the controlling creature also rolls a saving throw, and the undead uses the better result. &nl;Critical Success The target is unaffected and is temporarily immune for 24 hours. &nl;Success The target is unaffected. &nl;Failure The undead creature becomes a minion under your control. The spell gains a duration of 1 minute, but it is dismissed if you or an ally attacks the minion undead. &nl;Critical Failure As failure, but the duration is 1 hour.
Directed Channel				KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Directed Channel			SOURCEPAGE:p.123	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 04.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,04	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=04																				DESC:You can shape the energy you channel in a single direction, reaching farther and in a more directed fashion. When you cast a version of harm or heal that has an area, you can make its area a 60-foot cone instead of a 30-foot emanation.
Improved Communal Healing		KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Improved Communal Healing	SOURCEPAGE:p.123	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 04.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,04	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=04			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Communal Healing											DESC:You can direct excess channeled energy outward to benefit an ally. You can grant the Hit Points you would regain from Communal Healing to any one creature within the range of your heal spell instead of yourself. You can also use Communal Healing when you target only yourself with a heal spell, though if you do, you must grant the additional healing to someone other than yourself.
Necrotic Infusion [One-Action]	KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Necrotic Infusion			SOURCEPAGE:p.123	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 04.CLERIC.CONCENTRATE.METAMAGIC	PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,04	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=04			PRETEXT:Prerequisites harmful font, evil alignment									DESC:You pour negative energy into your undead subject to empower its attacks. If the next action you use is to cast harm to restore Hit Points to a single undead creature, the target then deals an additional 1d6 negative damage with its melee weapons and unarmed attacks until the end of its next turn. If the harm spell is at least 5th level, this damage increases to 2d6, and if the harm spell is at least 8th level, the damage increases to 3d6.
Cast Down [One-Action]			KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Cast Down				SOURCEPAGE:p.123	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 06.CLERIC.CONCENTRATE.METAMAGIC	PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,06	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=06			PRETEXT:Prerequisites harmful font or healing font									DESC:The sheer force of your faith can bring a foe crashing down. If the next action you use is to cast harm or heal to damage one creature, the target is knocked prone if it takes any damage from the spell. If the target critically fails its save against the spell, it also takes a -10-foot status penalty to its Speed for 1 minute.
Divine Weapon [Free-Action]		KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Divine Weapon			SOURCEPAGE:p.123	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 06.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,06	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=06																				DESC:Frequency once per turn &nl;Trigger You finish Casting a Spell using one of your divine spell slots on your turn. &nl;You siphon residual spell energy into a weapon you're wielding. Until the end of your turn, the weapon deals an additional 1d4 force damage. You can instead deal an additional 1d6 damage of an alignment type that matches one of your deity's alignment components. As usual for aligned damage, this can damage only creatures of the opposite alignment.
Selective Energy				KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Selective Energy			SOURCEPAGE:p.123	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 06.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,06	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=06																				DESC:As you call down divine power, you can prevent some enemies from benefiting or some allies from being hurt. When you cast a version of harm or heal that has an area, you can designate a number of creatures equal to your Charisma modifier (minimum 1) that are not targeted by the spell.
Steady Spellcasting			KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Steady Spellcasting		SOURCEPAGE:p.123	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 06.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,06	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=06																				DESC:Confident in your technique, you don't lose spells easily. If a reaction would disrupt your spellcasting action, attempt a DC 15 flat check. If you succeed, your action isn't disrupted.
Advanced Domain				KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Advanced Domain			SOURCEPAGE:p.123	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 08.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,08	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=08			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Domain Initiate											DESC:Your studies or prayers have unlocked deeper secrets of your deity's domain. You gain an advanced domain spell from one of your domains (as listed in Table 8-2: Domains on page 441). Increase the number of Focus Points in your focus pool by 1. Special You can select this feat multiple times. Each time, you must select a different advanced domain spell from a domain for which you have an initial domain spell.																																																																																																																															STACK:YES	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE					BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Advanced Domain Spell|1
Align Armament [One-Action]		KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Align Armament			SOURCEPAGE:p.124	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 08.CLERIC.DIVINE.EVOCATION		PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,08	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=08			PRETEXT:Prerequisites chaotic, evil, good, or lawful deity								DESC:Frequency once per round &nl;You bring a weapon into metaphysical concordance with your deity's beliefs. When you select this feat, choose chaotic, evil, good, or lawful. Your choice must match one of your deity's alignment components. This action has the trait corresponding to the chosen alignment component. When you use this action, you touch a weapon. For 1 round, that weapon deals an additional 1d6 damage of the chosen type to creatures of the opposed alignment. For example, if you chose good, the weapon would deal an extra 1d6 good damage to evil creatures. If you Align an Armament again, any previously aligned armament loses its additional damage. Special You can select this feat a second time, choosing your deity's other alignment component. When you Align an Armament, you can choose either alignment component.																																																									STACK:NO	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:STRING|Chaotic|Evil|Good|Lawful
Channeled Succor				KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Channeled Succor			SOURCEPAGE:p.124	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 08.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,08	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=08			PRETEXT:Prerequisites healing font												DESC:You can remove conditions with divine grace. You can sacrifice one heal spell you've prepared in your extra slots from healing font to cast one of the following spells instead: remove curse, remove disease, remove paralysis, or restoration. The spell is heightened to the same level as the heal spell you sacrificed.
Cremate Undead				KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Cremate Undead			SOURCEPAGE:p.124	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 08.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,08	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=08																				DESC:Your positive energy sets undead alight. When you use a heal spell to damage undead, each undead that takes damage also takes persistent fire damage equal to the spell's level.
Emblazon Energy				KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Emblazon Energy			SOURCEPAGE:p.124	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 08.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,08	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=08			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Emblazon Armament											DESC:With elemental forces, you make your emblazoned symbols more potent. When you Emblazon an Armament, you can choose from the following effects instead of the effects listed in that feat. These effects have the same restrictions as the base options. &nl;Shield Choose acid, cold, electricity, fire, or sonic. The wielder gain the shield's circumstance bonus to saving throws against that damage type and can use Shield Block against damage of that type. The shield also gains resistance to that damage type equal to half your level if you have a domain spell with a trait matching that type (such as fire). &nl;Weapon Choose acid, cold, electricity, fire, or sonic. The weapon deals an extra 1d4 damage of that type. Increase this extra damage to 1d6 if you have a domain spell with a trait matching that type (such as fire).
Castigating Weapon			KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Castigating Weapon		SOURCEPAGE:p.125	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 10.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,10	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=10			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Holy Castigation											DESC:The force of your deity's castigation strengthens your body so you can strike down the wicked. After you damage a fiend using a heal spell, your weapon or unarmed Strikes deal extra good damage to fiends equal to half the level of the heal spell until the end of your next turn. This is cumulative with any good damage the weapon already deals (such as from a holy rune).
Heroic Recovery [One-Action]		KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Heroic Recovery			SOURCEPAGE:p.125	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 10.CLERIC.CONCENTRATE.METAMAGIC	PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,10	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=10			PRETEXT:Prerequisites healing font, good alignment									DESC:The restorative power of your healing invigorates the recipient. If the next action you use is to cast heal targeting a single living creature and the target regains Hit Points from the spell, it also gains three bonuses until the end of its next turn: a +5-foot status bonus to its Speed, a +1 status bonus to attack rolls, and a +1 status bonus to damage rolls.
Improved Command Undead			KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Improved Command Undead		SOURCEPAGE:p.125	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 10.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,10	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=10			PRETEXT:Prerequisites harmful font, Command Undead, evil alignment						DESC:Undead creatures find it all but impossible to resist your commands. When you use Command Undead, if the undead succeeds at its save but doesn't critically succeed, it is your minion for 1 round. If the undead fails its save, it is your minion for 10 minutes. If it critically fails, it is your minion for 24 hours.
Replenishment Of War			KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Replenishment Of War		SOURCEPAGE:p.125	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 10.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,10	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=10			PRETEXT:Prerequisites expert in your deity's favored weapon								DESC:Striking out against your enemies draws praise and protection from your deity. When you damage a creature with a Strike using your deity's favored weapon, you gain a number of temporary Hit Points equal to half your level, or equal to your level if the Strike was a critical hit. These temporary Hit Points last until the start of your next turn.
Defensive Recovery [One-Action]	KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Defensive Recovery		SOURCEPAGE:p.125	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 12.CLERIC.CONCENTRATE.METAMAGIC	PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,12	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=12			PRETEXT:Prerequisites harmful font or healing font									DESC:Your faith provides temporary protection in addition to healing. If the next action you use is to cast harm or heal on a single target and the target regains Hit Points from the spell, it also gains a +2 status bonus to AC and saving throws for 1 round.
Domain Focus				KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Domain Focus			SOURCEPAGE:p.125	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 12.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,12	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=12			PRETEXT:Prerequisites one or more domain spells										DESC:Your devotion to your deity's domains grows greater, and so does the power granted to you. If you have spent at least 2 Focus Points since the last time you Refocused, you recover 2 Focus Points when you Refocus instead of 1.
Emblazon Antimagic			KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Emblazon Antimagic		SOURCEPAGE:p.125	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 12.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,12	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=12			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Emblazon Armament											DESC:Your deity's symbol protects against offensive magic. When you Emblazon an Armament, you can choose from the following effects instead of the effects listed in that feat. These effects have the same restrictions as the base options. &nl;Shield When the wielder has the shield raised, they gain the shield's circumstance bonus to saving throws against magic, and they can use Shield Block against damage from their enemies' spells. &nl;Weapon When the weapon's wielder critically hits with the weapon, they can attempt to counteract a spell on their target, using their level as the counteract level. If they attempt to do so, the emblazoned symbol immediately disappears.
Shared Replenishment			KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Shared Replenishment		SOURCEPAGE:p.125	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 12.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,12	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=12			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Replenishment of War										DESC:When your deity blesses your warlike acts, you can extend that favor to your allies. You can grant the temporary Hit Points from Replenishment of War to an ally within 10 feet instead of gaining them yourself. You can grant these temporary Hit Points to a different ally each time, meaning you might be able to grant them to multiple creatures in a single turn.
Deity's Protection			KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Deity's Protection		SOURCEPAGE:p.125	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 14.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,14	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=14			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Advanced Domain											DESC:When you call upon your deity's power to fulfill the promise of their domain, you gain divine protection. After you cast a domain spell, you gain resistance to all damage until the start of your next turn. The amount of resistance is equal to the level of the domain spell you cast.
Extend Armament Alignment		KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Extend Armament Alignment	SOURCEPAGE:p.125	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 14.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,14	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=14			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Align Armament											DESC:The alignment you impose on a weapon lasts much longer. The duration of Align Armament increases to 1 minute.
Fast Channel				KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Fast Channel			SOURCEPAGE:p.125	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 14.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,14	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=14			PRETEXT:Prerequisites harmful font or healing font									DESC:Divine power is always at your fingertips, swiftly responding to your call. When you cast harm or heal by spending 2 actions, you can get the effects of the 3-action version instead of the 2-action version. You can do this with harm if you have harmful font or heal if you have healing font (or both if you have Versatile Font).
Swift Banishment [Reaction]		KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Swift Banishment			SOURCEPAGE:p.126	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 14.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,14	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=14																				DESC:Trigger You critically hit a creature that is not on its home plane. &nl;Requirements You have a banishment spell prepared. &nl;The force of your blow sends your victim back to its home plane. You expend a banishment spell you have prepared, affecting the creature you critically hit without needing to cast the spell. The creature can attempt to resist the spell as normal.
Eternal Bane				KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Eternal Bane			SOURCEPAGE:p.126	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 16.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,16	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=16			PRETEXT:Prerequisites evil alignment											DESC:A life of evil has made you a nexus for your deity's vile power. You're continuously surrounded by a bane spell with a spell level equal to half your level (rounded up). The radius is 15 feet, and you can't increase it. You can Dismiss the spell; if you do, it returns automatically after 1 minute.
Eternal Blessing				KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Eternal Blessing			SOURCEPAGE:p.126	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 16.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,16	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=16			PRETEXT:Prerequisites good alignment											DESC:Your good deeds have brought your deity's grace to you for all of eternity. You're continuously surrounded by a bless spell with a spell level equal to half your level (rounded up). The radius is 15 feet, and you can't increase it. You can Dismiss the spell; if you do, it returns automatically after 1 minute.
Resurrectionist				KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Resurrectionist			SOURCEPAGE:p.126	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 16.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,16	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=16																				DESC:You can cause a creature you bring back from the brink of death to thrive and continue healing. When you restore Hit Points to a dying creature or bring a dead creature back to life and restore Hit Points to it, you grant that creature fast healing 5 for 1 minute. This fast healing ends if the creature is knocked unconscious.
Domain Wellspring				KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Domain Wellspring			SOURCEPAGE:p.126	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 18.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,18	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=18			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Domain Focus												DESC:The intensity of your focus grows from the investment you've placed in your domains. If you have spent at least 3 Focus Points since the last time you Refocused, you recover 3 Focus Points when you Refocus instead of 1.
Echoing Channel [One-Action]		KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Echoing Channel			SOURCEPAGE:p.127	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 18.CLERIC.CONCENTRATE.METAMAGIC	PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,18	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=18																				DESC:When you pull forth positive or negative energy, you also create a smaller pocket of that energy. If the next action you use is to cast a 2-action harm or heal to heal or damage a single creature, choose one additional creature adjacent to either you or the target. Target that creature with a 1-action version of the same spell. This spell is the same level as the 2-action harm or heal you cast and doesn't cost another spell slot.
Improved Swift Banishment		KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Improved Swift Banishment	SOURCEPAGE:p.127	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 18.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,18	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=18			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Swift Banishment											DESC:You easily banish creatures with your weapon. You can use Swift Banishment as long as you have a spell slot of 5th level or higher remaining, even if you don't have banishment prepared. You must sacrifice a prepared spell of 5th level or higher, and the banishment effect you create is heightened to the level of that spell. Your weapon serves as the special material component of banishment, causing the target to take the -2 penalty to its save against any banishment you cast using Swift Banishment.
Avatar's Audience				KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Avatar's Audience			SOURCEPAGE:p.121	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 20.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,20	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=20																				DESC:Your extensive service has made you a lesser herald of your deity, which affords you certain privileges. First, any creature you encounter knows instinctively that you speak for your deity. Second, if you conduct the commune ritual to contact your deity, you don't have to pay any cost and you automatically get a critical success. Third, once per day, you can cast plane shift as a divine innate spell, but only to travel to the realm of your deity. When you cast it this way, its casting time is 1 minute, your religious symbol is a sufficient tuning fork for this spell, and you appear exactly where you want to be. If you're in your deity's realm due to this spell, you can return to the point you left when you cast it by spending a single action, which has the concentrate and divine traits.
Maker Of Miracles				KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Maker Of Miracles			SOURCEPAGE:p.121	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 20.CLERIC				PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,20	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=20			PRETEXT:Prerequisites miraculous spell											DESC:You are a conduit for truly deific power. You gain an additional 10th-level spell slot.
Metamagic Channel [Free-Action]	KEY:Cleric Feat ~ Metamagic Channel			SOURCEPAGE:p.121	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Cleric Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 20.CLERIC.CONCENTRATE		PREVARGTEQ:ClericCL,20	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=20																				DESC:Deep understanding of divine revelations into the nature of vital essence allows you to freely manipulate the effects of your positive or negative energy. Use 1 metamagic action that you can perform that normally takes 1 action and can be applied to the harm or heal spell. If you use it in this way, its effects apply only to a harm or heal spell.






###Block: Druid Feats
# Ability Name					Unique Key						Source Page		Category of Ability	Type														Required Class		Required Non-Monster Lvl	Required Text									Var. Must Be Lower				Define							Description																																																																																																																																																Stackable?	Multiple?	Choose		Bonus Ability Pool				Modify VAR									Allow Follower			Allowed Companions
Animal Companion					KEY:Druid Feat ~ Animal Companion		SOURCEPAGE:p.133	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 1.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,01	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=01			PRETEXT:Prerequisites animal order													DEFINE:AnimalCompanionLVL|0				DESC:You gain the service of a young animal companion that travels with you on your adventures and obeys any simple commands you give it to the best of its abilities. See Animal Companions on page 214 for more information.																																																																																																																										BONUS:VAR|AnimalCompanionLVL|TL					FOLLOWERS:Animal Companion|1	COMPANIONLIST:Animal Companion|Animal Companion ~ Badger,Animal Companion ~ Bear,Animal Companion ~ Bird,Animal Companion ~ Cat,Animal Companion ~ Dromaesaur,Animal Companion ~ Horse,Animal Companion ~ Snake,Animal Companion ~ Wolf
Leshy Familiar					KEY:Druid Feat ~ Leshy Familiar		SOURCEPAGE:p.133	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 1.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,01	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=01			PRETEXT:Prerequisites leaf order													DEFINE:FamiliarLVL|0					DESC:You gain a leshy familiar, a Tiny plant that embodies one of the many spirits of nature. Other than taking the form of a plant instead of an animal, this familiar uses all the same rules as other familiars, which are detailed on page 217.																																																																																																																							BONUS:VAR|FamiliarLVL|TL						FOLLOWERS:Familiar|1		COMPANIONLIST:Familiar|Familiar ~ Leshy
Reach Spell [One-Action]			KEY:Druid Feat ~ Reach Spell			SOURCEPAGE:p.134	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 1.CONCENTRATE.DRUID.METAMAGIC			PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,01	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=01																													DESC:You can extend the range of your spells. If the next action you use is to Cast a Spell that has a range, increase that spell's range by 30 feet. As is standard for increasing spell ranges, if the spell normally has a range of touch, you extend its range to 30 feet.
Storm Born						KEY:Druid Feat ~ Storm Born			SOURCEPAGE:p.134	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 1.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,01	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=01			PRETEXT:Prerequisites storm order																					DESC:You are at home out in the elements, reveling in the power of nature unleashed. You do not take circumstance penalties to ranged spell attacks or Perception checks caused by weather, and your targeted spells don't require a flat check to succeed against a target concealed by weather (such as fog).
Widen Spell [One-Action]			KEY:Druid Feat ~ Widen Spell			SOURCEPAGE:p.134	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 1.DRUID.MANIPULATE.METAMAGIC			PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,01	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=01																													DESC:You manipulate the energy of your spell, causing it to spread out and affect a wider area. If the next action you use is to Cast a Spell that has an area of a burst, cone, or line and does not have a duration, increase the area of that spell. Add 5 feet to the radius of a burst that normally has a radius of at least 10 feet (a burst with a smaller radius is not affected). Add 5 feet to the length of a cone or line that is normally 15 feet long or smaller, and add 10 feet to the length of a larger cone or line.
Wild Shape						KEY:Druid Feat ~ Wild Shape			SOURCEPAGE:p.134	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 1.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,01	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=01			PRETEXT:Prerequisites wild order																					DESC:You are one with the wild, always changing and adapting to meet any challenge. You gain the wild shape order spell, which lets you transform into a variety of forms that you can expand with druid feats.
Call Of The Wild					KEY:Druid Feat ~ Call Of The Wild		SOURCEPAGE:p.134	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 2.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,02	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=02																													DESC:You call upon the creatures of nature to come to your aid. You can spend 10 minutes in concert with nature to replace one of the spells you've prepared in one of your druid spell slots with a summon animal or summon plants and fungi spell of the same level.
Enhanced Familiar					KEY:Druid Feat ~ Enhanced Familiar		SOURCEPAGE:p.134	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 2.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,02	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=02			PRETEXT:Prerequisites a familiar																					DESC:You infuse your familiar with additional primal energy, increasing its abilities. You can select four familiar or master abilities each day, instead of two.
Order Explorer					KEY:Druid Feat ~ Order Explorer		SOURCEPAGE:p.134	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 2.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,02	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=02																													DESC:You have learned the secrets of another druidic order, passing whatever rites of initiation that order requires and gaining access to its secrets. Choose an order other than your own. You gain a 1st-level feat that lists that order as a prerequisite, and you are now a member of that order for the purpose of meeting feat prerequisites. If you commit acts anathema to your new order, you lose all feats and abilities requiring that order but retain your other druid feats and abilities. You don't gain any of the other benefits of the order you chose. Special You can take this feat multiple times. Each time you do, you must choose a different order other than your own.
Poison Resistance [One-Action]		KEY:Druid Feat ~ Poison Resistance		SOURCEPAGE:p.135	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 2.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,02	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=02																													DESC:Your affinity for the natural world grants you protection against some of its dangers. You gain poison resistance equal to half your level, and you gain a +1 status bonus to saving throws against poisons.
Form Control [One-Action]			KEY:Druid Feat ~ Form Control			SOURCEPAGE:p.135	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 4.DRUID.MANIPULATE.METAMAGIC			PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,04	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=04			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Strength 14, Wild Shape																			DESC:With additional care and effort, you can take on an alternate form for a longer period of time. If your next action is to cast wild shape, wild shape's spell level is 2 lower than normal (minimum 1st level), but you can remain transformed for up to 1 hour or the listed duration (whichever is longer). You can still Dismiss the form at any time, as permitted by the spell.
Mature Animal Companion				KEY:Druid Feat ~ Mature Animal Companion	SOURCEPAGE:p.135	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 4.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,04	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=04			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Animal Companion												DEFINE:CompanionIsMature|0				DESC:Your animal companion grows up, becoming a mature animal companion, which grants it additional capabilities. See the animal companion rules on page 214 for more information. Your animal companion is better trained than most. During an encounter, even if you don't use the Command an Animal action, your animal companion can still use 1 action on your turn that round to Stride or Strike.																																																																																														BONUS:VAR|CompanionIsMature|1|TYPE=BASE
Order Magic						KEY:Druid Feat ~ Order Magic			SOURCEPAGE:p.135	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 4.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,04	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=04			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Order Explorer																				DESC:You have delved deeper into the teaching of a new order, gaining access to a coveted order spell. Choose an order you have selected with Order Explorer. You gain the initial order spell from that order. Special You can take this feat multiple times. Each time you do, you must choose a different order you have selected with Order Explorer.
Thousand Faces					KEY:Druid Feat ~ Thousand Faces		SOURCEPAGE:p.135	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 4.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,04	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=04			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Wild Shape																					DESC:Your form is as mutable as the weather, changing to meet your whim. You add the forms listed in humanoid form to your wild shape list.
Woodland Stride					KEY:Druid Feat ~ Woodland Stride		SOURCEPAGE:p.135	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 4.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,04	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=04			PRETEXT:Prerequisites leaf order																					DESC:You can always find a path, almost as if foliage parted before you. You ignore any difficult terrain caused by plants, such as bushes, vines, and undergrowth. Even plants manipulated by magic don't impede your progress.
Green Empathy					KEY:Druid Feat ~ Green Empathy		SOURCEPAGE:p.136	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 6.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,06	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=06			PRETEXT:Prerequisites leaf order																					DESC:You can communicate with plants on a basic level and use Diplomacy to Make an Impression on them and to make very simple Requests of them. Non-creature plants typically can't fulfill most requests you might ask of them unless you have access to other magic such as speak with plants. Because of your affiliation with the leaf order, plants have a sense that you support them, so you gain a +2 circumstance bonus on your check to Make a Request of a plant using Green Empathy.
Insect Shape					KEY:Druid Feat ~ Insect Shape			SOURCEPAGE:p.136	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 6.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,06	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=06			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Wild Shape																					DESC:Your understanding of life expands, allowing you to mimic a wider range of creatures. Add the forms in insect form to your wild shape list. Whenever you use wild shape to polymorph into the non-flying insect form listed in pest form, the duration is 24 hours instead of 10 minutes.
Steady Spellcasting				KEY:Druid Feat ~ Steady Spellcasting	SOURCEPAGE:p.136	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 6.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,06	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=06																													DESC:Confident in your technique, you don't lose spells easily. If a reaction would disrupt your spellcasting action, attempt a DC 15 flat check. If you succeed, your action isn't disrupted.
Storm Retribution [Reaction]			KEY:Druid Feat ~ Storm Retribution		SOURCEPAGE:p.136	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 6.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,06	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=06			PRETEXT:Prerequisites storm order, tempest surge order spell																DESC:Trigger An opponent adjacent to you critically hits you with a melee weapon or melee unarmed attack.&nl;Requirements You have at least 1 available Focus Point.&nl;You lash out, directing a burst of storming fury toward a creature that has harmed you. You cast tempest surge on the triggering opponent and push that creature, moving it 5 feet away from you if it fails its Reflex save, or 10 feet if it critically fails. This movement is forced movement.
Ferocious Shape					KEY:Druid Feat ~ Ferocious Shape		SOURCEPAGE:p.136	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 8.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,08	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=08			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Wild Shape																					DESC:You have mastered the shape of ferocious dinosaurs. Add the forms listed in dinosaur form to your wild shape list. Whenever you use wild shape to take a form that grants you a specific Athletics modifier, you gain a +1 status bonus to your Athletics checks.
Fey Caller						KEY:Druid Feat ~ Fey Caller			SOURCEPAGE:p.136	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 8.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,08	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=08																													DESC:You have learned some of the tricks the fey use to bend primal magic toward illusions and trickery. Add illusory disguise, illusory object, illusory scene, and veil to your spell list as primal spells.
Incredible Companion				KEY:Druid Feat ~ Incredible Companion	SOURCEPAGE:p.137	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 8.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,08	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=08			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Mature Animal Companion																			DESC:Your animal companion continues to grow and develop. It becomes a nimble or savage animal companion (your choice), gaining additional capabilities determined by the type of companion (page 214).																																																																																																																							BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Incredible Companion|1
Soaring Shape					KEY:Druid Feat ~ Soaring Shape		SOURCEPAGE:p.137	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 8.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,08	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=08			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Wild Shape																					DESC:Wings free you from the shackles of the ground below. Add the bat and bird forms in aerial form to your wild shape list. If you have Insect Shape, you also add the wasp form to your wild shape list. If you have Ferocious Shape, you also add the pterosaur form to your wild shape list. Whenever you use wild shape to gain a form that grants you a specific Acrobatics modifier, you gain a +1 status bonus to Acrobatics checks.
Wind Caller						KEY:Druid Feat ~ Wind Caller			SOURCEPAGE:p.137	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 8.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,08	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=08			PRETEXT:Prerequisites storm order																					DESC:You bid the winds to lift and carry you through the air. You gain the stormwind flight order spell. Increase the number of Focus Points in your focus pool by 1.
Elemental Shape					KEY:Druid Feat ~ Elemental Shape		SOURCEPAGE:p.137	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 10.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,10	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=10			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Wild Shape																					DESC:You understand the fundamental elements of nature such that you can imbue them into your body and manifest as a living embodiment of those elements. Add the forms in elemental form to your wild shape list. Whenever you're polymorphed into another form using wild shape, you gain resistance 5 to fire.
Healing Transformation [One-Action]		KEY:Druid Feat ~ Healing Transformation	SOURCEPAGE:p.137	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 10.DRUID.METAMAGIC					PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,10	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=10																													DESC:You can take advantage of shapechanging magic to close wounds and patch injuries. If your next action is to cast a non-cantrip polymorph spell that targets only one creature, your polymorph spell also restores 1d6 Hit Points per spell level to that creature. This is a healing effect.
Overwhelming Energy [One-Action]		KEY:Druid Feat ~ Overwhelming Energy	SOURCEPAGE:p.137	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 10.DRUID.MANIPULATE.METAMAGIC			PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,10	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=10																													DESC:With a complex gesture, you call upon the primal power of your spell to overcome enemies' resistances. If the next action you use is to Cast a Spell, the spell ignores an amount of the target's resistance to acid, cold, electricity, fire, or sonic damage equal to your level. This applies to all damage the spell deals, including persistent damage and damage caused by an ongoing effect of the spell, such as the wall created by wall of fire. A creature's immunities are unaffected.
Plant Shape						KEY:Druid Feat ~ Plant Shape			SOURCEPAGE:p.138	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 10.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,10	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=10			PRETEXT:Prerequisites leaf order or Wild Shape																			DESC:You can take the form of a plant creature. Add the forms listed in plant form to your wild shape list; if you don't have wild shape, you can instead cast plant form once per day, heightened to the highest spell level you can cast. Whenever you're polymorphed into another form using wild shape, you gain resistance 5 to poison.
Side By Side					KEY:Druid Feat ~ Side By Side			SOURCEPAGE:p.138	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 10.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,10	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=10			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Animal Companion																				DESC:You and your animal companion fight in tandem, distracting your foes and keeping them off balance. Whenever you and your animal companion are adjacent to the same foe, you are both flanking that foe with each other, regardless of your actual positions.
Dragon Shape					KEY:Druid Feat ~ Dragon Shape			SOURCEPAGE:p.138	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 12.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,12	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=12			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Soaring Shape																					DESC:You can take on the form of some of the world's most fearsome creatures. Add the forms listed in dragon form to your wild shape list. Whenever you're polymorphed into another form using wild shape, you gain resistance 5 to your choice of acid, cold, electricity, fire, or poison.
Green Tongue					KEY:Druid Feat ~ Green Tongue			SOURCEPAGE:p.138	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 12.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,12	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=12			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Green Empathy																					DESC:You share a special kinship with all things green and living. You (and your leshy familiar, if you have one) are constantly under the effects of speak with plants. Most non-creature plants recognize you as a druid of the leaf order and are friendly to you.
Primal Focus					KEY:Druid Feat ~ Primal Focus			SOURCEPAGE:p.138	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 12.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,12	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=12																													DESC:Your connection to nature is particularly strong, and the spirits of nature flock around you, helping you replenish your focus. If you have spent at least 2 Focus Points since the last time you Refocused, you recover 2 Focus Points when you Refocus instead of 1.
Primal Summons					KEY:Druid Feat ~ Primal Summons		SOURCEPAGE:p.138	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 12.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,12	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=12			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Call of the Wild																				DESC:Whenever you summon an ally, you can empower it with the elemental power of air, earth, fire, or water. You gain the primal summons order spell.
Specialized Companion				KEY:Druid Feat ~ Specialized Companion	SOURCEPAGE:p.139	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 14.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,14	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=14			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Incredible Companion				PREVARLT:SpecializedCompanionTaken,3	DEFINE:SpecializedCompanionTaken|0			DESC:Your animal companion continues to grow in power and ability, and it is now cunning enough to become specialized. Your animal companion gains one specialization of your choice. (See the Animal Companion section on page 214.) Special You can select this feat up to three times. Each time, add a different specialization to your companion.																																																																																								STACK:YES	MULT:YES	CHOOSE:NOCHOICE	BONUS:ABILITYPOOL|Specialized Companion|1	BONUS:VAR|SpecializedCompanionTaken|1
Timeless Nature					KEY:Druid Feat ~ Timeless Nature		SOURCEPAGE:p.139	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 14.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,14	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=14																													DESC:With primal magic sustaining you, you cease aging. The overflowing primal energy gives you a +2 status bonus to saves against diseases and primal magic.
Verdant Metamorphosis				KEY:Druid Feat ~ Verdant Metamorphosis	SOURCEPAGE:p.139	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 14.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,14	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=14			PRETEXT:Prerequisites leaf order																					DESC:You transform into a plant version of yourself. You gain the plant trait and lose any trait that's inappropriate for your new form (typically humanoid for a PC, but also possibly animal or fungus). You can change from a form that looks mostly like your old self into a tree or any other non-creature plant as a single action, which has the concentrate trait. This has the same effect as tree shape, except you can turn into any kind of non-creature plant and your AC is 30. If you rest for 10 minutes while transformed into a noncreature plant during daylight hours under direct sunlight, you recover half your maximum Hit Points. If you take your daily rest in this way, the rest restores you to maximum Hit Points and removes all non-permanent drained, enfeebled, clumsy, and stupefied conditions, as well as all poisons and diseases of 19th level or lower.
Effortless Concentration [Free-Action]	KEY:Druid Feat ~ Effortless Concentration	SOURCEPAGE:p.139	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 16.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,16	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=16																													DESC:Trigger Your turn begins.nl;You maintain a spell with hardly a thought. You immediately gain the effects of the Sustain a Spell action, allowing you to extend the duration of one of your active druid spells.
Impaling Briars					KEY:Druid Feat ~ Impaling Briars		SOURCEPAGE:p.139	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 16.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,16	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=16			PRETEXT:Prerequisites leaf order																					DESC:You can fill an area with devastating briars that impale and impede your foes. You gain the impaling briars order spell. Increase the number of Focus Points in your focus pool by 1.
Monstrosity Shape					KEY:Druid Feat ~ Monstrosity Shape		SOURCEPAGE:p.139	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 16.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,16	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=16			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Wild Shape																					DESC:You can transform into a powerful magical creature. Add the purple worm and sea serpent forms listed in monstrosity form to your wild shape list. If you have Soaring Shape, add the phoenix form listed in aerial form to your wild shape list.
Invoke Disaster					KEY:Druid Feat ~ Invoke Disaster		SOURCEPAGE:p.139	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 18.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,18	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=18			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Wind Caller																					DESC:You can invoke nature's fury upon your foes. You gain the storm lord order spell. Increase the number of Focus Points in your focus pool by 1.
Perfect Form Control				KEY:Druid Feat ~ Perfect Form Control	SOURCEPAGE:p.139	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 18.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,18	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=18			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Form Control, Strength 18																			DESC:Thanks to magic and muscle memory, you can stay in your alternate forms indefinitely; you may have even forgotten your original form. When you use Form Control, instead of lasting 1 hour, wild shape is permanent until you Dismiss it.
Primal Wellspring					KEY:Druid Feat ~ Primal Wellspring		SOURCEPAGE:p.139	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 18.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,18	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=18			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Wild Focus																					DESC:Your reservoir of Focus Points is a deep wellspring. If you have spent at least 3 Focus Points since the last time you Refocused, you recover 3 Focus Points when you Refocus instead of 1.
Hierophant's Power				KEY:Druid Feat ~ Hierophant's Power		SOURCEPAGE:p.139	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 20.DRUID							PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,20	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=20			PRETEXT:Prerequisites legendary in Nature																				DESC:You have entwined yourself with the natural world, and its full power flows through you. You gain an additional 10th-level spell slot.
Leyline Conduit [One-Action]			KEY:Druid Feat ~ Leyline Conduit		SOURCEPAGE:p.139	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 20.CONCENTRATE.DRUID.MANIPULATE.METAMAGIC	PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,20	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=20																													DESC:Frequency once per minute&nl;You can cast your spells effortlessly by tapping into the leylines of the world. If your next action is to Cast a Spell of 5th level or lower that has no duration, you don't expend the prepared spell as you cast it.
True Shapeshifter [Two-Actions]		KEY:Druid Feat ~ True Shapeshifter		SOURCEPAGE:p.139	CATEGORY:CLASS FEAT	TYPE:Druid Class Feat.Class Feat.FEAT 20.CONCENTRATE.DRUID					PREVARGTEQ:DruidCL,20	PREPCLEVEL:MIN=20			PRETEXT:Prerequisites Dragon Shape, Wild Shape																			DESC:You transcend the limitations of form. While under the effects of wild shape, you can change into any other form on your wild shape list; if the durations of the forms would vary, use the shorter of the two durations. Once per day, you can transform into a kaiju, with the effects of nature incarnate; if you have Plant Shape, you can instead transform into a green man.

